## Typo / Typography - EXACT SPECIFICATIONS

### Typefaces
- **Headings**: Playfair Display (elegance and trustworthiness)
- **Body Text**: Inter (clarity and digital readability)

### Typography Hierarchy - EXACT SIZES FROM BRAND BOOK

#### H1: Main Heading
- **Font**: Playfair Display Regular
- **Size**: 48px / 3rem (desktop), 36px / 2.25rem (mobile)
- **Line height**: 1.2
- **Color**: Forest Green (#2F5D50)
- **Usage**: Page titles, main section headings

#### H2: Section Heading
- **Font**: Playfair Display Regular
- **Size**: 36px / 2.25rem (desktop), 28px / 1.75rem (mobile)
- **Line height**: 1.3
- **Color**: Forest Green (#2F5D50)
- **Usage**: Major section headings, article titles

#### H3: Subsection Heading
- **Font**: Playfair Display Regular
- **Size**: 24px / 1.5rem (desktop), 20px / 1.25rem (mobile)
- **Line height**: 1.4
- **Color**: Forest Green (#2F5D50)
- **Usage**: Subsection headings, feature headings

#### H4: Minor Heading
- **Font**: Inter Semi-Bold
- **Size**: 20px / 1.25rem (desktop), 18px / 1.125rem (mobile)
- **Line height**: 1.4
- **Color**: Forest Green (#2F5D50)
- **Usage**: Minor headings, UI section titles

#### Body Text
- **Font**: Inter Regular
- **Size**: 16px / 1rem (minimum requirement)
- **Line height**: 1.6
- **Color**: Dark Gray (#333333)
- **Paragraph spacing**: 1rem (16px)

#### Subheading Treatment
- **Font**: Inter Medium
- **Size**: 18px / 1.125rem
- **Line height**: 1.5
- **Color**: Dark Gray (#333333)

#### Caption and Small Text
- **Font**: Inter Regular
- **Size**: 14px / 0.875rem (captions), 12px / 0.75rem (small text)
- **Line height**: 1.5
- **Color**: Medium Gray (#666666)

### Typography Rules
- **Minimum body text size**: 16px / 1rem across all devices
- **Use relative units**: rem, em rather than fixed px
- **Line length**: Aim for 45-75 characters per line
- **Contractions**: Use contractions (you're, we'll, it's) for conversational tone
- **Sentence case**: Use sentence case for headings and titles (first word capitalized only)
- **Numbers**: Spell out one through nine, use numerals for 10 and above

## Logo Usage - EXACT SPECIFICATIONS

### Logo Specifications
- **Minimum size**: 100px wide for digital, 1 inch for print
- **Clear space**: Equal to height of "L" around all sides
- **Proportions**: Never stretch, compress, rotate, or distort
- **Colors**: Forest Green (#2F5D50) for text, Muted Turquoise (#A7D6D1) for dot

### Logo Versions
- **Primary**: Full color on light backgrounds
- **Monochrome Black**: #000000 on white/light backgrounds
- **Monochrome White**: #FFFFFF on dark backgrounds
- **Reversed**: White text with Muted Turquoise dot on dark backgrounds
- **Simplified**: "L" icon with turquoise dot for small applications (min 32px)

### Favicon and App Icon
- **Background**: Forest Green (#2F5D50) square
- **"L" character**: White (#FFFFFF), centered
- **Dot**: Muted Turquoise (#A7D6D1) in lower right quadrant
- **Rounded corners**: 20% radius of icon size

## Tone of Voice

### Voice Characteristics
- **Friendly, Calm, and Encouraging**: Warm, patient, positive, reassuring, supportive
- **Clarity Over Cleverness**: Straightforward, concise, purposeful, accessible, natural
- **Conversational but Professional**: Write as speaking to a respected colleague

### Writing Principles
- **Active voice**: "Lyyli will help you write emails" not "Emails will be written with Lyyli's help"
- **Direct address**: Use "you" and "your" for personal connection
- **Specific and concrete**: Use examples and specifics rather than vague claims
- **Concise**: Aim for 15-20 word average sentence length
- **Professional without stiffness**: Maintain professionalism while being approachable

### Microcopy Examples
- **Success**: "Your email template has been saved. It's ready whenever you need it."
- **Loading**: "Creating your social post. This will take just a moment..."
- **Empty states**: "No templates yet. Create your first one to save time on future messages."
- **Errors**: "It looks like we need a bit more information. Could you add a few details?"

## UI Guidelines

### Layout Principles
- **Generous whitespace**: Ample breathing room between elements
- **Clear visual hierarchy**: Important elements receive visual prominence
- **Consistent patterns**: Predictable layouts and interactions
- **Grid system**: 8px base unit, 12-column desktop, 8-column tablet, 4-column mobile

### Button Specifications
- **Primary Button**:
  - Background: Forest Green (#2F5D50)
  - Text: White (#FFFFFF)
  - Border radius: 8px
  - Padding: 12px 24px
  - Text: Inter Semi-Bold, 16px
  - Hover: Slightly lighter Forest Green (#3A6A5C)

- **Secondary Button**:
  - Background: White (#FFFFFF)
  - Text: Forest Green (#2F5D50)
  - Border: 2px solid Forest Green (#2F5D50)
  - Border radius: 8px
  - Padding: 12px 24px
  - Text: Inter Semi-Bold, 16px

### Form Elements
- **Text Inputs**:
  - Background: White (#FFFFFF)
  - Border: 1px solid Light Gray (#E5E5E4)
  - Border radius: 8px
  - Height: 48px (standard), 40px (compact)
  - Padding: 12px 16px
  - Text: Inter Regular, 16px, Dark Gray (#333333)
  - Focus: 2px Forest Green (#2F5D50) border

### Cards
- **Background**: White (#FFFFFF)
- **Border**: 1px solid Light Gray (#E5E5E4), optional
- **Border radius**: 12px
- **Shadow**: 0px 4px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05), optional
- **Padding**: 24px
- **Title**: Playfair Display, 20px, Forest Green (#2F5D50)

### Responsive Design
- **Breakpoints**:
  - Small: 320px-639px (mobile)
  - Medium: 640px-1023px (tablet)
  - Large: 1024px-1439px (desktop)
  - Extra Large: 1440px+ (large desktop)
- **Mobile-first approach**: Design core experiences for mobile first
- **Touch targets**: Minimum 44×44px for interactive elements

## Imagery & Illustration Style

### Photography Style
- **Mood**: Calm and serene, warm and inviting, natural and authentic
- **Style**: Clean and uncluttered, soft focus with clarity
- **Editing**: Soft contrast, slightly desaturated, warm undertones
- **Subjects**: Collaborative environments, solo entrepreneurs, communication moments

### Illustration Guidelines
- **Style**: Gentle, soft vector or hand-drawn
- **Characteristics**: Rounded forms, minimal detail, gentle line work, subtle textures
- **Scenes**: Calm, collaborative environments, supportive interactions, productive spaces
- **Colors**: Forest Green and Muted Turquoise as primary, accented by Soft Rose

### Icon System
- **Style**: Rounded, simple, UI-integrated
- **Characteristics**: Rounded corners (2px radius minimum), consistent stroke weight (2px)
- **Grid**: 24×24px base with 1px padding
- **Format**: SVG for crisp rendering at all sizes
- **Sizes**: Optimize for 16px, 24px, 32px, and 48px usage

## ICP Terminology
- **English**: Use "professional service company" or "professional service organization" instead of "expert team"
- **Finnish**: Use "asiantuntijaorganisaatio" instead of "asiantuntijatiimi"
- **Target Audience**: Solo entrepreneurs, micro-businesses (1-5 employees), small teams, non-technical professionals

## Blog Post Formatting
- **H2 headings (##)**: Must use Playfair Display font for visual prominence
- **H3 subheadings (###)**: Should use Playfair Display Regular, 24px/1.5rem
- **Use double line breaks** between major chapters/sections for better readability
- **Remove horizontal lines (---)**: Use spacing instead
- **Maintain consistent spacing** and visual hierarchy throughout
- **Pull quotes**: Use Playfair Display italic for emphasis

## Animation Guidelines
- **Timing**: 150-300ms for responsiveness
- **Easing**: Natural easing functions (ease-in-out)
- **Purpose**: Guide attention, provide feedback, establish relationships
- **Subtlety**: Gentle, understated animations that don't distract
- **Performance**: Optimize to avoid affecting page performance

## Accessibility Requirements
- **Contrast**: Meet WCAG 2.1 AA standards
- **Focus indicators**: 2px Forest Green (#2F5D50) outline for all interactive elements
- **Keyboard support**: Logical tab order, clear focus visibility
- **Screen readers**: Semantic HTML, proper ARIA attributes
- **Alt text**: Descriptive, concise, functional descriptions

## Implementation Notes
- **Font loading**: Use Google Fonts for Playfair Display and Inter
- **CSS variables**: Implement brand colors as CSS custom properties
- **Responsive typography**: Use CSS clamp() for fluid scaling
- **Color testing**: Test across devices and in color blindness simulations
- **Brand consistency**: Apply these guidelines across all digital and print materials

- Use primary logo on light backgrounds
- Use white logo on dark backgrounds
